This paper is primarily focused on optimization algorithms for deep learning, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper specifically investigates the interaction between adaptive gradient methods and learning rate schedules, which is a common issue in computer vision (cs.CV), natural language processing (cs.CL), and neural networks (cs.NE). Additionally, the paper presents empirical and theoretical retrospectives on the generalization of adaptive gradient methods, which is relevant to the broader field of artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
